LMS Desktop Assistant v1.11\par
\ulnone\b0 May 27, 2011\par
\par
\lang1043\ul Functionality\ulnone :\ul\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\ulnone Files can now be manually marked as "already synchronized", so they will not be uploaded until they have been modified. This is handy to prevent reuploading of exercises which were already uploaded using the Exercises tab.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Files can now be manually marked as "not synchronized", to force a reupload on the next synchronization.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}A portable version of the program is now available instead of the old non-administrator install.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The program now supports the Chamilo 2.0 platform.\line\b Remark: \b0 The Chamilo implementation has support for the new advanced options of the "Fill in the Blanks" exercises. However, if you are using a version of Chamilo which does not yet support advanced options like default scores, you should use the platform "\b Chamilo 2.0 test\b0 " for better compatibility.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\lang1033\par
